                    <h2 class="text-center">Education
                        
                    </h2>
                    <p>I knew I wanted to be a programmer all the way back in my freshman year at Freedom High School.  I took a course in Visual Basic and I loved it.  I continued to take classes in Java, C++, and web development for the duration of high school and by the end of those four years, there was no question what I'd major in at college.</p>
                    <p>Attending college at Shippensburg University in Pennsylvania, I pursued a bachelor's degree in Computer Science with a Software Engineering concentration.  Thanks to a fantastic group of professors, I received a strong education in the fundamentals and patterns of software development.  I joined and became Vice President of our school's chapter of Upsilon Pi Epsilon, the Computer Science Honor's Society.  I ended my time at Shippensburg University with a 3.8 GPA and Summa Cum Laude honors. </p>
